Rust Run - Day 4
Rust Run - Day 4
It is a series of part of the Rust Run Series, 2018. future, promise, delay, and deferred refer to constructs used for synchronizing program execution in some concurrent programming languages. They describe an object that acts as a proxy for a result that is initially unknown, usually because the computation of its value is yet incomplete. This meetup will be a discussion on the use of futures in rust using the futures crate. https://docs.rs/futures/0.2.1/futures/

Dark Funnel campaign
Dark Funnel campaign
We want to understand where Firefox downloads come from. So far, we know that 30% of Firefox installs come from the official Mozilla website or from known partners. The other 70% come from mystery download sources that we call â€œthe dark funnelâ€. Some are friendly sites, but others put users at risk of getting old editions, a bad experience or even malicious installs. Help Firefox understand whatâ€™s in the dark funnel, by participating in this campaign and spreading the light!

Dark Funnel in Sri Lanka
Dark Funnel in Sri Lanka
We want to understand where Firefox downloads come from. So far, we know that 30% of Firefox installs come from the official Mozilla website or from known partners. The other 70% come from mystery download sources that we call â€œthe dark funnelâ€. Some are friendly sites, but others put users at risk of getting old editions, a bad experience or even malicious installs. Help Firefox understand whatâ€™s in the dark funnel, by participating in this campaign and spreading the light!

Privacy month campaign-2019
January Privacy Month Campaign is a community-led campaign/initiative to celebrate International Data Privacy Day. The campaign was originated by Mozilla India in 2016 and is intended to be a global campaign each year. Become a Community Coordinator in Your Region!

The Mozilla Reps program is open to all Mozillians who are 18 years of age and above. Before you become a Mozilla Rep, you must follow our learning process so that you can become a good Community Coordinator in your region.

Community Coordinators are not a power structure over other Mozillians, instead they are here to help, empower and motivate other Mozillians to contribute to Mozilla projects.

There are tons of opportunities you can benefit from joining this program:

  • Access to a global community which includes people from many different countries and cultural backgrounds.
  • Direct support from Mozilla to help you empower others in your region to advance Mozillaâ€™s goals.
  • Opportunity to help your local community grow.
  • Grow your leadership and communication skills and build networks with new people from many different countries around the globe.
  • Amplify Mozillaâ€™s impact in your local region and functional area.

If you want to learn more about our program, you might want to connect with one of our currently active Mozilla Reps in your region, so you can learn and understand the challenges and opportunities of this program.

Find Mozilla Reps from your region

Major requirements:

  • The applicant needs to be at least 18 years old
  • The applicant needs to be active within Mozilla for at least 6 months

If you want to learn more about the Reps Program Selection Criteria please check here.

The Mozilla Reps application process involves two simple steps. Ready? Let's get started!

Thanks for your interest in making the Web better with Mozilla!
